1
00:00:15,541 --> 00:00:16,541
[LION]
Yay!

2
00:00:16,625 --> 00:00:18,541
Look at the pretty snow!

3
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:19,791
Wow!

4
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:22,250
--[BELLE squeaks]
--[LION giggles]

5
00:00:23,583 --> 00:00:24,750
Are you ready for a reload?

6
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,291
Hook me up!

7
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:30,083
It's not a real snow robot till
you give her a huge antenna.

8
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:31,416
Wouldn't it be more appropriate

9
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,625
to decorate your creature
with a Christmas theme?

10
00:00:33,708 --> 00:00:35,125
Oh, that's a great idea!

11
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:36,666
It's only common sense--

12
00:00:38,875 --> 00:00:40,791
Who's responsible
for that snowball?!

13
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:42,625
[KAREN]
Sorry. Thought I saw a Yeti.

14
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:44,375
We gotta retreat! Let's book it!

15
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:45,583
[LION laughs]

16
00:00:45,666 --> 00:00:46,416
[LION]
Run away!

17
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,750
[YAYOI]
Stop right there!

18
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:51,166
--[KARIN, KAREN, LION laughing]
--[YAYOI panting]

19
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:53,541
Oh! Hey up there.
Good morning, Nina!

20
00:00:53,625 --> 00:00:55,541
Looks like you're
having fun this morning.

21
00:00:55,625 --> 00:00:57,416
[LION]
Can you get me a weapon?

22
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:58,500
Weapon?

23
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,416
Be careful with this, please.

24
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:08,375
This is awesome!

25
00:01:08,458 --> 00:01:11,125
I'll use my special ice power
to defeat the evil Yeti!

26
00:01:11,208 --> 00:01:15,666
--[YAYOI screams]
--[LION laughs]

27
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:19,666
[RINO]
Now then.

28
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:21,791
I know we're all looking
forward to winter break,

29
00:01:21,875 --> 00:01:25,083
but before that happens, you all
must complete semester finals.

30
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:26,333
[STUDENTS groan]

31
00:01:26,416 --> 00:01:28,000
[RINO] The practical
exam for this term

32
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:30,458
has been scheduled
as a tournament.

33
00:01:31,791 --> 00:01:33,166
[RINO] Please consult
the bulletin board

34
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:35,833
for your match times
and written test information.

35
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:37,416
[STUDENTS]
Okay.

36
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,208
'Scuse me, but is there going to
be another school announcement?

37
00:01:40,291 --> 00:01:42,791
Due to the accident
during--I-I mean,

38
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:45,291
unfortunate event
during the last broadcast,

39
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:46,666
we're skipping this one.

40
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,041
I understand.

41
00:01:48,125 --> 00:01:49,500
Well that's a real bummer.

42
00:01:49,583 --> 00:01:52,708
I liked the whole student
council "soap opera" drama.

43
00:01:54,208 --> 00:01:55,666
[MIZUKI sighs]

44
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:58,250
I really wanted to do the
winter term announcement.

45
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:00,541
Goodness gracious,
don't forget that we've both

46
00:02:00,625 --> 00:02:02,041
already stepped down
from our posts,

47
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:04,250
so it's time to leave things
to our successors now.

48
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,625
But I had a plan.

49
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,250
I was gonna hijack
their broadcast

50
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:09,041
for my glorious proposal.

51
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:11,083
[STUDENTS chattering]

52
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:12,583
[YUKO] I wonder what
the first-years are doing

53
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:13,958
for their practical.

54
00:02:14,041 --> 00:02:16,041
[MIZUKI]
I heard it was a tournament.

55
00:02:16,125 --> 00:02:17,458
[YUKO]
Oh, really?

56
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:19,208
That's rough.

57
00:02:19,291 --> 00:02:21,125
Their strength in battle
will clearly be ranked

58
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:22,875
after such an exercise.

59
00:02:22,958 --> 00:02:24,458
Poor girls.

60
00:02:24,541 --> 00:02:28,083
It can be hard to know how the
ACLA sees you as a Logicalist.

61
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:36,208
I wonder who I'm gonna
be fighting first.

62
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:37,416
What?!

63
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:38,875
There's no way I can
fight our mistress!

64
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:40,416
[YAYOI] Karen,
you need to be more concerned

65
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,583
about your written exam.

66
00:02:41,666 --> 00:02:43,833
[KAREN]
You know that's a lost cause!

67
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:49,208
They're really starting you off
with a tough opponent.

68
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:50,458
[footsteps]

69
00:02:50,541 --> 00:02:53,000
Oh. Hey there, we were
just talking about you.

70
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:54,750
Nina, it's so awful!

71
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,958
They want us to fight,
so what are we gonna do?

72
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:58,083
What are you talking about?

73
00:02:58,166 --> 00:03:00,041
There's only one thing to do.

74
00:03:00,125 --> 00:03:02,041
I won't hold
anything back, either.

75
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,125
[LION]
Okay.

76
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:04,916
I'll give it my all, too!

77
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:11,000
--[harp playing]
--[STUDENTS chattering]

78
00:03:12,958 --> 00:03:16,750
[footsteps]

79
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:17,791
[PRINCIPAL]
Hm?

80
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,541
[NINA]
Aren't you cold out here?

81
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,083
[NINA] Principal,
I've come to see you

82
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:28,333
because I have a request.

83
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,958
Please give me a chance
to go on a mission.

84
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:33,291
I don't care what kind of
assignment it is.

85
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:37,958
[NINA] In the past, an incident
occurred almost every day.

86
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:40,208
And even though the world
is at peace now,

87
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:41,583
I know there has to be some way

88
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:44,125
for me to prove
the value of my powers.

89
00:03:44,208 --> 00:03:47,666
But I fear
if things continue...

90
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:52,958
[PRINCIPAL]
Do you hate this school?

91
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:56,041
[NINA] I like it now,
but you see...

92
00:03:56,125 --> 00:03:59,125
...there's something
more important I need to do.

93
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:00,666
You should know.

94
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:03,500
I'm very proud of the time
I spent protecting our world,

95
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:05,166
as a Logicalist.

96
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:12,458
[NINA] I will rank first
in all my finals this term,

97
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:14,416
both practical and written.

98
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:17,083
And I'll even compete
in exams for upperclassmen.

99
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:18,458
So please.

100
00:04:18,541 --> 00:04:21,916
Give me a chance to return
to my position at ALCA.

101
00:04:23,166 --> 00:04:27,750
Whether it be hot or cold,

102
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:29,541
that which goes around
in this life

103
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:32,458
will never be far
out of someone's reach.

104
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,125
[PRINCIPAL]
Can you see the flame

105
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,833
that's been lit inside you?

106
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:39,166
[NINA gasps]

107
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,208
[PRINCIPAL]
Yes.

108
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:43,083
That's right.

109
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:47,583
It may not be something that
you'd recognize in yourself.

110
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:51,250
And yet, you will
come across those people

111
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:55,750
who'll give you that precious
fire, which burns so brightly.

112
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:12,583
[NINA]
Who's in there this late?

113
00:05:13,708 --> 00:05:15,208
Ha!

114
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:17,583
[LION whines]

115
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:18,750
[KAGURA]
What's wrong?

116
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,583
I can tell you're scared!

117
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:26,125
[gasps]

118
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:32,166
[KAGURA]
You really are a meek mouse.

119
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,041
[LION]
I don't think I can do this.

120
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:40,083
Are you sure these practices
will make me stronger?

121
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,458
Positive.

122
00:05:42,916 --> 00:05:45,083
Lion, as soon as you learn
to control your emotions,

123
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:47,416
you'll immediately become
a top-class Logicalist.

124
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:50,000
Even as strong as those
on active duty.

125
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:52,541
You're a lot like I was
when I was your age.

126
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:54,625
Meaning you used to be
a strong fighter too?

127
00:05:54,708 --> 00:05:57,708
Are you implying that
I'm not strong anymore?

128
00:05:57,791 --> 00:06:00,458
The two of us share
many of the same qualities.

129
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:01,625
Huh?

130
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:04,458
Extremely strong,
such that it's a burden.

131
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:06,208
Huh?

132
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:07,708
[KAGURA] That's why the
other staff members

133
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:10,208
begged me to give you
these extra lessons.

134
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,541
Okay, so does that mean

135
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,333
if you were to Trance
with my covenant Waffle

136
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:17,625
that you'd end up
talking funny like me?

137
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:18,958
Maybe?

138
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:21,041
[LION laughs]

139
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:23,458
Just for that,
today's lesson will be harder.

140
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:27,625
[LION]
Oh, c'mon, that's not fair!

141
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:35,333
[LION]
Hey, Nina. Nina.

142
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:37,416
Can you teach me
this small section?

143
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:40,958
[NINA] How many "small sections"
have I taught you today?

144
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:43,041
Sorry, but I really am
just asking you

145
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,458
about the parts of the book
I don't understand.

146
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:47,416
[BELLE whines]

147
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,041
[sighs]

148
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:51,083
--[NINA] Which part?
--[giggles]

149
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:52,791
[LION]
Here! Question four.

150
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,041
[NINA]
You should be able to solve it

151
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:56,083
with the same formula
I showed you last time.

152
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:57,208
[LION]
Oh, really?

153
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:58,166
Thanks, Nina.

154
00:06:58,250 --> 00:06:59,375
You're the best!

155
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:00,583
[NINA] Think through
the problems yourself

156
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:01,708
before asking for help.

157
00:07:01,791 --> 00:07:03,000
[LION whines]

158
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:06,000
You just have to
carry the one right here.

159
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:16,583
[NINA] Hey, didn't I hear you
in the training hall last night?

160
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:17,625
[BELLE squeaks]

161
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,166
[NINA]
What were you doing in there?

162
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:23,083
Were you with Miss Kagura?

163
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:25,500
--[BELLE whines]
--[LION] Well, um...

164
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:28,625
I know, Belle, it's okay.

165
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:30,041
So, uh.

166
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:32,750
That was my detention.

167
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:37,208
The thing is, there's like a lot
about me that's not working out.

168
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,041
[laughs]

169
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,291
I see.

170
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:45,041
Huh? What's the matter?

171
00:07:45,125 --> 00:07:46,166
[MAHIRO]
Nina!

172
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:47,958
I need you to teach me
this stuff too.

173
00:07:48,041 --> 00:07:49,625
My mistress has her
hands full with Karen,

174
00:07:49,708 --> 00:07:52,041
so I'd be eternally grateful
if you could tutor me as well.

175
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:54,083
We've covered so much
material this semester

176
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:55,833
that I can't cram it
all in one night!

177
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:56,791
[NINA]
Which part?

178
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:58,208
[KARIN]
Question seven.

179
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:00,750
[MAHIRO] I don't get the parts
that I don't get, okay?

180
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:11,833
[STUDENTS chattering]

181
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:14,916
[YAYOI] Nina's been
concentrating like that

182
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,166
for a while.

183
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,041
She must be gearing up
for the practical today.

184
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:19,500
[LION]
I bet you're right.

185
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:21,416
Doesn't she know that I
plan on placing first

186
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,666
in this tournament?

187
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,583
Which means that I'll be
taking you down, too.

188
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,416
No way! I'm not gonna
lose to you!

189
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,583
[YAYOI chuckles]

190
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:33,083
[BELLE whines]

191
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,208
[LION]
Come on, Waffle!

192
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,625
Do your best!

193
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:51,416
[WAFFLE] Let's do our best
together, Lion!

194
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:08,583
[NINA]
Don't worry about them.

195
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:10,291
I know your strength.

196
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:14,000
[AMOL] Yeah! I'll protect
you no matter what, Nina.

197
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:28,708
Hey, Nina.

198
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,583
I don't stand a chance
against you.

199
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:33,416
But I'm still gonna
give it my all today.

200
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,041
Let's both do our best.

201
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:36,416
I know I will.

202
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,166
[RINO]
Here we go.

203
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,000
I'd like the two of
you ladies to fight

204
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:42,875
to the best of your abilities.

205
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:45,875
The first round of our
practical exam starts...

206
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:47,250
...right now!

207
00:10:01,916 --> 00:10:02,666
Ha!

208
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,708
[gasps]

209
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,708
Let's go.

210
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:14,333
[NINA gasps]

211
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,500
[LION]
Trance Change.

212
00:10:18,583 --> 00:10:19,541
Ha!

213
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:23,250
[groans]

214
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:30,833
If I keep this up,
I might actually beat her!

215
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:33,833
I'm surprised to see
Nina struggling so much.

216
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:36,875
Yeah, she kinda doesn't
seem like herself out there.

217
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:42,750
Let me guess.

218
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:45,458
You've been hiding your strength
all this time, haven't you?

219
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:46,333
[LION]
Hm?

220
00:10:46,416 --> 00:10:47,583
What are you talking about?

221
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:50,000
[NINA]
Trance Change!

222
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:51,791
Don't play dumb with me!

223
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,375
You're scaring me!

224
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,500
[NINA yells]

225
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:01,541
Trance Change!

226
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:07,958
[LION]
Why?

227
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,166
I won't hold
anything back either.

228
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,666
[LION]
I don't quite understand.

229
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,208
But it's an exam.

230
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:21,333
So I think it's only proper
that I really... give it my all.

231
00:11:21,416 --> 00:11:23,208
[NINA] So do you
pity me or something?

232
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:24,250
Huh?

233
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,750
[NINA]
Logic Drive!

234
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,708
Logic Drive!

235
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:41,208
Oh, Nina! Lion!

236
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:43,375
They hit at the same time.

237
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:46,333
But they both still have
their Protective Shields up.

238
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:50,083
[panting]

239
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:51,500
[NINA groans]

240
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:52,958
[footsteps]

241
00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:54,041
[LION]
Whoa, Nina!

242
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,916
Are you okay?

243
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,958
Get back, we're still
in the middle of our match.

244
00:11:59,041 --> 00:11:59,875
[LION]
I know.

245
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:01,416
Sorry.

246
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,000
I just wanted--

247
00:12:03,083 --> 00:12:04,750
to make sure you're all right.

248
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:07,416
I don't need your pity, Lion.

249
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,416
What do you mean?
I just wanted to check on you

250
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,041
'cause it looked like you
were struggling a little.

251
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:12,916
That's the definition of pity!

252
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,416
But that's not fair!

253
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,666
Everyone worries when their
friends are having problems!

254
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:18,333
Are we friends?

255
00:12:18,416 --> 00:12:20,208
Then why are you
keeping secrets?

256
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:21,291
[LION gasps]

257
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:23,791
A good friend
would never do that!

258
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:24,833
[gasps]

259
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:32,208
[LION whimpers]

260
00:12:32,291 --> 00:12:34,375
[LION sobs]

261
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:37,458
Wait. Are you crying? Why?

262
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:39,500
[BELLE squeaks]

263
00:12:40,375 --> 00:12:41,333
[gasps]

264
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:42,500
Wha...?

265
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:49,541
Are you the sharp-tongued girl
who just broke Lion's heart?

266
00:12:57,291 --> 00:13:00,208
[STUDENTS scream]

267
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:02,500
[BELLE squeaks]

268
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:04,500
[NINA]
Look out!

269
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:07,000
She's so out of it that
she doesn't recognize Belle.

270
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:09,958
Miss Kagura, this reminds me of
how she looked in the courtyard

271
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:11,500
the first time she ever Tranced.

272
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:13,833
Yes, but this is even worse.

273
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:15,041
[RINO]
Lion, stop!

274
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:16,583
[KAGURA]
Get a hold of yourself!

275
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,750
--Lion!
--Lion!

276
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,000
Snap out of it!

277
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:23,125
[OTHERS yelling]

278
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,083
[LION gasps]

279
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:31,875
[LION]
Huh...?

280
00:13:36,625 --> 00:13:38,625
What am I--

281
00:13:38,708 --> 00:13:40,833
I'm so sorry!

282
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:42,083
I didn't mean to do this!

283
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:43,041
--[BELLE squeaks]
--[NINA] Lion!

284
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:45,000
[ROSA]
You down there.

285
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:48,708
Only her loved ones may
call her by that nickname.

286
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:57,916
[BELLE whimpers]

287
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,375
[BELLE whines]

288
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:16,583
[STUDENTS chatter]

289
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:17,750
[MAHIRO]
Yayoi!

290
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,166
How's it look?

291
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:21,000
I can't see her
through the storm!

292
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:23,750
Where on Septpia
could you be, Lion?

293
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,916
[RINO] Miss Kagura,
what should we do?

294
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,208
I'll go after her, okay?

295
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:28,666
[BELLE squeaks]

296
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,750
Fujisaki, please
contact the principal.

297
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:31,750
[RINO]
Got it!

298
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:33,083
[MAHIRO]
I wanna help you find her!

299
00:14:33,166 --> 00:14:33,916
[KARIN]
So do I!

300
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,166
[KAREN]
Me too!

301
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,250
Nina.

302
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,916
None of what happened
is your fault.

303
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,416
But--

304
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:42,833
Lion's the one who lost control
over her Trance's balance.

305
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:43,958
Don't worry,
you can leave the rest--

306
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:45,875
That's not it!

307
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:47,875
You don't understand.

308
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:51,625
Let me go and find her.

309
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:55,458
[sighs]

310
00:14:55,541 --> 00:14:56,416
Very well.

311
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,333
But, keep Belle with you.

312
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:01,291
She has the power to restore
Lion's emotional balance.

313
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:02,791
[BELLE squeaks]

314
00:15:02,875 --> 00:15:04,291
I understand.

315
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:06,833
We'll bring her back safely.

316
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:09,375
[KAGURA] Fujisaki and I
will come after you later.

317
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:10,958
Don't be reckless.

318
00:15:11,041 --> 00:15:11,833
[BELLE squeaks]

319
00:15:11,916 --> 00:15:13,000
[NINA gasps]

320
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:19,916
[NINA]
That light.

321
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,583
That must be Lion's power.

322
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:22,625
[BELLE squeaks]

323
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:26,583
[gasps]

324
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,625
--[NINA grunts]
--[BELLE squeaks]

325
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:38,625
Lion, it's me!

326
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:43,000
[NINA]
Oh, no!

327
00:15:43,541 --> 00:15:45,083
[BELLE squeaks]

328
00:15:46,125 --> 00:15:48,083
You should be safe
in here, Belle.

329
00:15:51,916 --> 00:15:52,875
[NINA grunts]

330
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:57,750
[NINA grunts]

331
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,333
Trance Change now!

332
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:02,458
Logic Drive!

333
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:09,083
Trance Change again!

334
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:12,000
[NINA]
A little farther.

335
00:16:14,041 --> 00:16:15,750
[NINA]
We're almost there.

336
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:20,000
[NINA groans]

337
00:16:20,083 --> 00:16:21,875
[BELLE whines]

338
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,666
I'm okay.

339
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,000
Look at Lion.

340
00:16:25,083 --> 00:16:26,916
She has it way worse.

341
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,583
Wake up, Lion!

342
00:16:37,375 --> 00:16:38,333
[NINA]
Ha!

343
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:45,708
[exhales]

344
00:16:55,208 --> 00:16:57,666
[NINA]
Do it now, Belle!

345
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,000
[BELLE squeaks]

346
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:03,500
[BELLE squeals]

347
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:13,333
[BELLE squeaks]

348
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:20,750
[NINA groans]

349
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,958
[NINA gasps]

350
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:26,166
[NINA grunts]

351
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:27,500
[NINA]
Please.

352
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:28,541
Wake up.

353
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:30,666
You've gotta wake up!

354
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,875
Lion!

355
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:37,041
[BELLE whines]

356
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:41,625
[LION]
N-Nina, is that you?

357
00:17:45,125 --> 00:17:47,541
Please. Forgive me, Nina.

358
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:48,666
I'm sorry!

359
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,583
[LION sobs]

360
00:17:50,666 --> 00:17:52,166
[NINA]
Lion.

361
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,250
Listen to me.

362
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,125
This isn't your fault.

363
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:57,791
I'm the one who threw you
off balance today.

364
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:59,541
[LION whimpers]

365
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:02,250
I'm really sorry, Lion.

366
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:05,041
I didn't mean to say
all that stuff to you.

367
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:07,166
Please, you don't
need to apologize.

368
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,500
It is I who is
in the wrong here.

369
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:11,833
[NINA]
"I"?

370
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:13,041
Don't talk that way.

371
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,541
[LION]
U-Um, well, I...

372
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:18,625
Just be... yourself.

373
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:21,250
Okay.

374
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,416
That's easy.

375
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,708
[NINA giggles]

376
00:18:27,291 --> 00:18:29,125
What a relief.

377
00:18:34,375 --> 00:18:35,833
[gasps]

378
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:37,125
What's the matter?

379
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:38,791
Get up, Nina!

380
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:44,750
[LION cries]

381
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,583
This is my fault.

382
00:18:46,666 --> 00:18:48,875
Look what I've done to you.

383
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:51,500
You can't die here! No way!

384
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:54,291
I have to get us out of
this storm and save you!

385
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:58,833
[LION]
I can't tell which way to go.

386
00:19:00,041 --> 00:19:02,208
But if I don't do something--

387
00:19:03,541 --> 00:19:05,291
[BELLE squeaks]

388
00:19:05,375 --> 00:19:07,583
[LION] Are you trying to say
that you'll lend me your power?

389
00:19:07,666 --> 00:19:09,041
[BELLE squeaks]

390
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:12,291
[LION]
Let's do it!

391
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:21,625
[BELLE] I have waited a long
time to offer you this oath.

392
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:26,833
I, Belle, swear to offer my
Logic to Liones Yelistratova. 

393
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,541
And I, Liones Yelistratova,
accept your oath.

394
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:31,666
And in return,
offer my Logic to you, Belle,

395
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:33,708
for as long as you may need it.

396
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:37,958
[BELLE] You've proven
yourself more than capable.

397
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,125
[LION]
Trance!

398
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:09,541
What's going on?

399
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:14,625
Hey, so, does it hurt anymore?

400
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,875
No.

401
00:20:19,958 --> 00:20:21,083
I feel better.

402
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:22,583
Thank you.

403
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:35,500
[RINO] The first year practical
exam has been cancelled now.

404
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:38,166
Grades will be calculated
based on your performance

405
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:39,750
on previous assignments.

406
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,416
I am so sorry.

407
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,000
What's more,

408
00:20:43,083 --> 00:20:46,250
we have no choice but to report
this entire incident to ALCA.

409
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:49,541
But Miss Fujisaki,
she's not at fault here.

410
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:53,750
I'll give them the details
and ALCA will decide fault.

411
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,625
I'm sure it'll take them
some time to figure out

412
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:57,666
how to handle this problem.

413
00:20:57,750 --> 00:21:01,208
It may or may not be determined
by the end of our winter break.

414
00:21:01,291 --> 00:21:02,875
Right.

415
00:21:02,958 --> 00:21:04,916
[RINO]
I have to say.

416
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,458
I'm happy the two
of you are safe.

417
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:16,500
You get big gold stars!

418
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,333
[LION]
I'm really sorry, Nina.

419
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:29,833
[NINA] Why do you keep
apologizing to me?

420
00:21:29,916 --> 00:21:32,166
[LION] Because I promised
to always support you,

421
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,541
but instead...

422
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:37,791
You wanna go back
to work at ALCA, right?

423
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:40,875
But once they read the report
about what happened...

424
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:42,041
[NINA sighs]

425
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:43,458
[LION] I wanted to
help you get back there,

426
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:46,041
but I'm just getting
in your way.

427
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:48,458
And I'm sorry about that.

428
00:21:50,916 --> 00:21:53,333
[NINA] I learned an
important lesson today.

429
00:21:53,416 --> 00:21:56,833
That I've got a longer way
to go than I thought.

430
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:59,750
So please don't apologize
to me anymore.

431
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:02,708
[NINA]
Liones.

432
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:05,250
Liones?

433
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:08,208
[NINA]
That's right.

434
00:22:08,291 --> 00:22:10,208
Isn't that what you wanted?

435
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,541
I like Lion way better.

436
00:22:13,625 --> 00:22:15,000
Well?

437
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,708
[LION giggles]

438
00:22:22,416 --> 00:22:23,833
Lion it is.

439
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:27,666
Oh, Nina!

440
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:28,708
[NINA gasps]

441
00:22:29,666 --> 00:22:30,916
[BELLE squeaks]

442
00:22:34,541 --> 00:22:36,833
[laughs]

443
00:22:36,916 --> 00:22:39,083
Gosh.

444
00:22:39,166 --> 00:22:44,000
[BOTH laugh]

445
00:22:44,083 --> 00:22:48,250
[LION, NINA] ♪ Many years
and months have passed ♪

446
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:52,208
♪ Since last I laid eyes
on my world ♪

447
00:22:52,291 --> 00:22:56,291
♪ Yet I have a wish that lasts ♪

448
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:59,916
♪ Even with time
my hope's never faded ♪

449
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:04,041
♪ If you take my hand,
you'll hear it too ♪

450
00:23:04,125 --> 00:23:10,041
♪ A soft and gentle voice ♪

451
00:23:10,125 --> 00:23:14,166
♪ As long as I
stay close to you ♪

452
00:23:14,250 --> 00:23:18,333
♪ Then both our hearts
will beat as one ♪

453
00:23:18,416 --> 00:23:22,500
♪ Show me a smile
There's no need for prayers ♪

454
00:23:22,583 --> 00:23:26,208
♪ Your heart lets me know
that you care ♪

455
00:23:26,291 --> 00:23:30,541
♪ A soul inside
that does beguile ♪

456
00:23:30,625 --> 00:23:33,291
♪ Shines as bright as the sun ♪

457
00:23:33,375 --> 00:23:38,583
♪ It calls out to me
It echoes inside ♪

458
00:23:38,666 --> 00:23:45,708
♪ Keeping beat with my heart
just like a song ♪

